    h2 Usage
    
    a(href="https://github.com/dynamicresponsemedia/drm-calendar" target="_blank") Visit GitHub Repo
    p at the moment only US style dates and times are used

    h3.drm-bold Initialize:

    pre new DrmCalendar(calendarClass = 'drm-calendar', @view = 'month', @addHolidays = yes);

    h4.drm-bold Options:
    ul.drm-unstyled-list
        li
            span.drm-bold calendarClass: 
            | classname of the calendar holder - default: drm-calendar
        li
            span.drm-bold view: 
            | first view when the calendar loads - default: month
            ul
                li month
                li week
                li date
        li
            span.drm-bold addHolidays: 
            | add holidays to calendar (US only for now) - default: yes

    h3.drm-bold Add events dynamically using the createEvent method
    p createEvent takes an object as its only argument

    pre.
        drmCalendar = new DrmCalendar();
        drmCalendar.createEvent(newEvent);

    h4.drm-bold Options:
    ul.drm-unstyled-list
        li
            span.drm-bold id: 
            | the event id number (DrmCalendar will add this for you - don't add this yourself)
        li
            span.drm-bold name: 
            | name of your event
        li
            span.drm-bold recurrance: 
            | how often the event will occur
            ul
                li
                    span.drm-bold yearly: 
                    | once per year
                li
                    span.drm-bold monthly: 
                    | once per month
                li
                    span.drm-bold biweekly: 
                    | every other week
                li
                    span.drm-bold weekly: 
                    | once per week
                li
                    span.drm-bold daily: 
                    | every single day
                li
                    span.drm-bold none: 
                    | exactly once
        li
            span.drm-bold month: 
            | month of your event - full name of month not abbreviations or month number
        li
            span.drm-bold year: 
            | year of your event - for non-recurring events only
        li
            span.drm-bold eventDate: 
            | date of event
        li
            span.drm-bold time: 
            | time of event ex. 2:30pm - omit for all day events
        li
            span.drm-bold day: 
            | day of the week - array of days of the week - full name of day not abbreviations or day number - can be an array ex. ['Saturday', 'Sunday']
        li
            span.drm-bold dayNum: 
            | day number - ex. 1 for first occurance of day in month - use 'last' for the last occurance in the month
        li
            span.drm-bold type: 
            | event type - so far holiday is the only type that has any effect
        li
            span.drm-bold notes: 
            | event notes - show up in the event view

    h4.drm-bold Examples:

    h5.drm-bold Yearly Event:
    
    pre.
        drmCalendar.createEvent({
            name: 'Thanksgiving',
            month: 'November',
            dayNum: 'last',
            day: ['Thursday'],
            type: 'holiday',
            recurrance: 'yearly',
            notes: 'Thanksgiving occurs on the last Thursday in November'
        });

    h5.drm-bold Monthly Event:

    pre.
        drmCalendar.createEvent({
            name: 'Rabbit Rabbit Day',
            eventDate: 1,
            type: 'fun day',
            recurrance: 'monthly',
            notes: 'Say Rabbit Rabbit for good luck this month'
        });

    h5.drm-bold Weekly Event:
    
    pre.
        drmCalendar.createEvent({
            name: 'Sleep In!',
            day: ['Sunday', 'Saturday']
            time: '9:00am'
            recurrance: 'weekly',
            notes: 'Thanksgiving occurs on the last Thursday in November'
        });

    h5.drm-bold Daily Event:
    
    pre.
        drmCalendar.createEvent({
            name: 'Eat Lunch',
            time: '12:00pm'
            recurrance: 'daily',
            notes: 'Eat a healthy lunch'
        });